New Records: Morocco equalled the biggest winning margin in 2025 qualifying after South Africa set the benchmark with a five-goal drubbing of Congo Brazzaville.
Key Match Events: Abde Ezzalzouli, Achraf Hakimi, and Soufiane Rahimi each scored once.
Serhou Guirassy scored a hat-trick as Guinea trounced Ethiopia 4-1.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Morocco qualify automatically for the AFCON as hosts, with the tournament due to start on December 21, 2025, and finish on January 18, 2026.
